o erase unwanted tastes and smells have transformed water into a highly industrialized food product divorced from its origins. The Taste of Water invites readers to question their own assumptions about what water does and should naturally taste like while exposing them to the invisible—but substantial—sensory labor involved in creating tap water.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDrinking waterxSensory evaluationzFrancey20th century. 0aDrinking waterxSensory evaluationzUnited Statesy20th century. 0aMunicipal water supplyzFrancey20th century. 0aMunicipal water supplyzUnited Statesy20th century. 0aWaterxPurificationxTaste and odor controlzFrancey20th century. 0aWaterxPurificationxTaste and odor controlzUnited Statesy20th century. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131921608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023z9783111318615oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520393561?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520393561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520393561/original  a978-3-11-131921-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DPMb2023